íŸ@bbdfabac6be9885b6ff052e80daa3fb92923064191ffbb52bfe22b6de8c5c55d⁄YTitle: title: path relative-to
Path: Examples
Content:
Find a relative path from two absolute paths.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '/home/viking' | path relative-to '/home'
viking

```
Find a relative path from absolute paths in list.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [ /home/viking, /home/spam ] | path relative-to '/home'
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ viking ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ spam   ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
Find a relative path from two relative paths.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'eggs/bacon/sausage/spam' | path relative-to 'eggs/bacon/sausage'
spam

```
íŸ@b3d9fdeaaf2a1906fc06d9f86f718ce0786a71215364b1e928c638967cc6ca47Ÿ“Title: title: path relative-to
Path: Notes
Content:
Can be used only when the input and the argument paths are either both

absolute or both relative. The argument path needs to be a parent of the input

path.
